<TEXT>
funeral services were held wednesday for a 
black man whose shooting death by police sparked two days of rioting 
and looting in vineland while a special panel convened on how to 
calm racial tensions 
community leaders had hoped the unrest following the sunday night 
shooting had subsided but four people were arrested wednesday 
including a man who scuffled with a television news crew said lee 
tofanelli a city spokesman 
the wpvitv news crew from philadelphia was attacked by a group 
of youths as they interviewed people in downtown vineland where 
rioting and looting broke out monday night tofanelli said 
news reporter dann cuellar was listed in stable condition at 
newcomb medical center in vineland with a broken nose and facial 
injuries hospital officials said a cameraman and sound technician 
were treated for minor injuries and discharged 
i feel no animosity toward those youngsters out there 
cuellar said in a telehone interview there is a lot of 
frustration a lot of anger here 
cuellars wallet and some television equipment were stolen the 
equipment was returned later tofanelli said 
allen fleming 23 was arrested on assault and robbery charges 
tofanelli said and three other people were arrested in a separate 
incident when they disobeyed police orders to leave the area the 
charges were not available 
about 200 people packed into truth baptist church in newfield for 
a twohour ceremony in remembrance of 26yearold samuel williams 
who was shot and killed by vineland police on sunday 
mayor harry curley met with community leaders and announced the 
formation of an eightmember special task force to find ways of 
restoring calm to the city 
were hoping this will be the first step curley said at an 
informal press conference at his city hall office were hoping 
that we can be assured there wont be any more outbreaks 
samuel clark president of the local chapter of the national 
association for the advancement of colored people thought the 
unrest would end with the memorial service 
theyre grieving but i dont think its going to be a 
destructive type of thing clark said 
mourners gathered outside the small white church in newfield 
about several miles north of vineland as the coffeecolored casket 
containing williams body was led to a black hearse 
they raised clenched fists in a symbol of black power as a choir 
sang oh how i love jesus 
williams body was taken to a funeral home and then to the state 
medical examiners office in newark for a second autopsy an initial 
autopsy was performed monday by the county coroner 
williams a father of two children was shot after he allegedly 
threatened officer paul letizia with a steel rod said police chief 
joseph cassisi 
williams who was wanted on drug and weapons charges was spotted 
by officers after police received an anonymous telephone call about 
a man on a bicycle carrying drugs cassisi said 
after being told he was under arrest williams picked up the rod 
and approached letizia swinging cassisi said letizia who is 
white fired two shots at williams hitting him both times the 
police chief said 
curley said letizia has been taken off street duty and put on 
special assignment the mayor said he did not plan to follow the 
demands of some blacks who want letizia suspended without pay 
pending the outcome of an investigation by the state attorney 
generals office 
curley said the task force would review the police departments 
relationship with the mostly minority community as well as the 
handling of citizen complaints he said a report was expected in 
about 30 days 
