the united states is urging israeli authorities 
to complete an investigation into the death of an arabamerican 
teenager and the disappearance of two other americans 
state department spokesman richard boucher said tuesday the 
united states wants israel to determine who killed a 14yearold 
americanborn youth in the west bank earlier this month 
a report by a scottish pathologist retained by the family of 
amjad jibril tawil said the youth was killed by a single gunshot 
wound amjad was born in denver but lived in the west bank for the 
last four years 
boucher said the state department had been in close touch with 
the youths family as well as with relatives of two other americans 
of palestinian origin who have been reported missing for more than 
10 days in israeliheld territory 
we certainly understand the tragedy of the situation and their 
agony boucher said weve been talking to their families weve 
been following up with the israeli authorities we urge the israeli 
authorities to conduct a full investigation 
the united states also condemned israels expulsion of five 
palestinians on sunday 
the expulsions brought to 60 the number of arabs deported for 
their alleged role in organizing the 20month uprising against 
israeli rule in the west bank and gaza strip 
we deplore these latest deportations boucher said these 
measures corrode the atmosphere within which the peace process must 
be moved forward and make it more difficult for israelis and 
palestinians to engage in constructive dialogue 
