a havanaborn republican state senator rode heavy 
support from miamis hispanic community tuesday to become the first 
cubanamerican elected to congress winning the seat held by the 
late claude pepper for nearly three decades 
with all precincts reporting in the ethnically divisive race 
state sen ileana roslehtinen 37 received 49638 votes or 53 
percent to 43759 or 47 percent for brooklynborn attorney gerald 
richman 
the 48yearold democrat who is jewish had been making his 
first run for elective office 
the race was made necessary by peppers death may 30 at 88 
pepper a democrat had held the seat since its inception 27 years 
ago 
the 93000plus turnout was nearly 51 percent far higher than 
normal for a special election and higher than election officials 43 
percent projection 
the outcome was delayed more than an hour late tuesday by a dade 
county elections computer problem that temporarily halted 
votecounting higher final counts for both candidates were revised 
early wednesday because of the counting problems 
the unofficial returns indicated that predominantly hispanic 
precincts with turnouts of more than 60 percent boosted ms 
roslehtinen with 80 to 90 percent margins while richman was 
favored by margins of 80 to 90 percent in predominantly black or 
nonlatin white precincts 
in her victory speech ms roslehtinen said she wanted to unify 
and heal the community and provide leadership which is based 
on acaring conscience and conservative convictions 
we do not have the luxury to waste time on divisive politics 
she told cheering supporters at the airport hilton hotel we must 
focus on what we have in common and not ponder on the negative 
richman addressing disappointed supporters at the clarion castle 
hotel in miami beach said we have done incredibly well and we 
did it on a positive theme 
he said ms roslehtinen outspent him and had campaign help from 
president bush vice president dan quayle and sen connie mack 
rfla 
the democrat noting that more hispanics turned out than blacks 
or nonhispanic whites said weve got to get everyone in this 
community to get out and exercise their right to vote if that had 
happened we would have won tonight 
the democrats mindful that august is vacation month for many 
miami residents had tried to build an absenteevote margin for 
richman but election officials said richman had only 3933 absentee 
votes to 3599 for ms roslehtinen 
