the fact is that a bill introduced by rep lee hamilton of 
indiana would factor raw politics into the financial equations of 
the fed creating nothing short of economic pandemonium 
hamilton and other critics complain that like the us supreme 
court the fed is autonomous guided by a handful of appointed 
experts it moves interest rates up and down as it pleases it is 
accountable to no one its deliberations are conducted in secret 
its decisions may not be appealed 
all that is true and let us be grateful the alternative at 
least the alternative favored by hamilton is to authorize the 
congressionally run general accounting office to audit the feds 
monetary transactions which are now protected from such scrutiny 
and recommend changes 
it is not difficult to see how this would give congress whose 
impulses are unfailingly political leverage over the feds 
decisions 
hamilton also wants to make the treasury secretary a voting 
member of the fed thereby enhancing white house influence too 
in justification he argues that the feds monetary policy is not 
democratic enough of course it isnt democratic it is not supposed 
to be democratic the genius of the federal reserve is precisely 
that it insulates monetary decisions from politics 
the purpose of the hamilton bill is as plain as it is alarming 
hamilton hopes to undermine the independence of the federal 
reserve the economys chief protection against a freewheeling 
freespending politically driven congress the mechanism may not be 
perfect but it works 
only at our enormous peril will congress be permitted to 
