japanese prime minister toshiki kaifu 
arrived today on a trip designed to foster closer ties and establish 
the diplomatic credentials of his new adminstration 
during his first overseas trip since taking office aug 9 kaifu 
hopes to use baseball diplomacy and meetings with us officials and 
academics to ease trade tensions between america and japan foreign 
ministry officials said 
kaifu was greeted here this morning by nobuo matsunaga japanese 
ambassador to the united states shunji yanai japanese consul 
