<TEXT>
sir peter scott a conservationist who pioneered 
the effort to save the worlds rain forests and helped launch the 
world wildlife fund is dead at age 79 
scott a world war ii naval hero and an olympic yachtsman died 
tuesday in bristols southmead hospital following a heart attack 
earlier in the day while visiting the western england city he would 
have been 80 on sept 14 
he was known internationally for his campaigns to save birds 
bears tigers and whales 
in his last years he was forced to defend his father capt 
robert falcon scott against revisionist historians who claimed the 
great polar explorer bungled the 191112 expedition in which he and 
four companions perished of cold and hunger 
scotts death was announced wednesday by the wildlife and 
wetlands trust which he began in 1946 at slimbridge on the severn 
river estuary where he lived he founded it as a haven for water 
birds after shooting a goose and seeing it die slowly 
i thought i wouldnt do that to my worst enemy so why should i 
do it to a goose he recalled 
scott was a cofounder in 1961 of the swissbased world wildlife 
fund now the world wide fund for nature he designed its panda logo 
and helped raise more than 60 million for 6000 conservation 
projects in 135 countries 
the fund is largely credited with saving the indian tiger and the 
polar bear and with pioneering efforts to save rain forests 
buckingham palace said queen elizabeth ii her husband prince 
philip and their son prince charles sent condolences to scotts 
widow philippa 
sir david attenborough the tv naturalist described scott as the 
patron saint of conservation one of the great figures who warned 
the world of what was happening and not only warned but did 
something about it 
scott was 2 when his father died in march 1912 in the antarctic 
snows after being beaten to the south pole by the norwegian roald 
amundsen the explorer left a note to his wife saying make the 
boy interested in natural history it is better than games 
his son said he felt having a hero for a father meant he had to 
do well in different fields 
scott became a celebrated bird artist won an olympic yachting 
bronze medal in 1936 was a thricedecorated naval commander in 
world war ii a champion glider pilot americas cup helmsman in 
1964 and the first briton to be knighted for services to 
conservation in 1973 
he wrote or illustrated nearly 40 books and an autobiography 
the eye of the wind in 1961 
scott was prominent in whalesaving efforts and said in 1987 
if the pressure is kept up all commercial whaling should cease 
and the only whales killed would be for subsistence by people like 
the eskimos who take small numbers and i think they should be 
allowed to go on doing so 
he led expeditions of explorers and naturalists to many parts of 
the world including three in his fathers footsteps to the 
antarctic which he called the last environmental frontier 
scott believed in the loch ness monster saying it was a family 
of prehistoric creatures living in the scottish lake he gave the 
animal a scientific name nessiteras rhombopteryx meaning ness 
monster with diamond fin 
scott and his family expressed anger in 1985 over a tv serial 
the last place on earth based on a debunking book by roland 
huntford called scott and amundsen it depicted his father as an 
incompetent loser and alleged that capt scotts wife kathleen had 
an affair with another norwegian explorer fridtjof nansen while 
her husband was battling in the antarctic 
they were very friendly but i dont believe for an instant that 
she had an affair with him sir peter said 
scott is survived by his two wives and three children in 1942 
he married the novelist elizabeth jane howard by whom he had a 
daughter the marriage was dissolved in 1951 and the same year he 
married his secretary philippa talbotponsonby who bore him a son 
and a daughter 
</TEXT>
