<TEXT>
the israeli army is creating a special unit to 
help put down the 20monthold palestinian uprising in the occupied 
territories after experimenting with soldiers specially trained in 
riot control an army spokesman said wednesday 
the move marks a break with israeli military tradition in which 
troops are trained mainly as combat soldiers for conventional 
warfare 
the new special force is intended to get regular combat troops 
out of the occupied west bank and gaza strip and back to standard 
training programs said col renaan gissin the armys deputy chief 
spokesman 
gissin said two experimental special companies have been 
operating in the occupied territories for several months their 
formation followed complaints by some officers that duty in the 
territories was cutting into regular training 
the decision to form a permanent new unit was made after the 
experimental companies proved effective in dealing with palestinians 
who have been waging an uprising against israeli rule in lands 
occupied in the 1967 middle east war gissin said 
at least 19 palestinians and two israeli soldiers were injured 
wednesday in new clashes in the occupied territories 
in the gaza strip town of khan yunis two soldiers were injured 
by stones and 11 palestinians were shot and wounded when troops 
opened fire during a stonethrowing melee the army and arab reports 
said 
six palestinians were shot and wounded in three other clashes in 
the seaside strip 
an army spokesman confirmed two arabs wounded in the west bank 
and said the military was investigating other reports 
at least 554 palestinians have been killed in clashes with 
soldiers or israeli civilians during the uprising thirtyeight 
israeli also have been slain 
these units will spend most of their service in one place 
gissin said adding they will know the area and the population 
better than troops that rotate in and out every three or four 
months 
the special unit dubbed the territories companies will 
receive specialized training on how to deal with stone and 
firebombthrowing youths attacking troops in cities and villages 
gissin said 
he said they would operate better in such situations than elite 
infantry units trained to fight regular forces on a battlefield or 
guerrillas attempting to infiltrate into the country 
the daily alhamishmar reported that new recruits are reluctant 
to be sent to the experimental forces which did more police duties 
than the more glamorous combat units but gissin denied the report 
we have had no problem in recruiting men and do not expect any 
when we enlarge the unit he said 
all israeli men do three years of compulsory military duty and 
serve in the reserves for up to 60 days a year until the age of 54 
often in the occupied territories most women serve for two years in 
noncombat units and later in the reserves until the age of 24 
gissin said the possibility of hurting soldiers morale by having 
them spend the majority of their threeyear military service among 
hostile civilians had been thoroughly examined by military 
psychologists 
of course we examined the issue and we are confident the 
soldiers will be ok he said 
