<TEXT>
the nations schools are being attacked by 
selfappointed censors who want to ban or restrict profane or 
satanic books and sanitize sex education classes an anticensorship 
group said wednesday 
people for the american way released its 7th annual report 
attacks on the freedom to learn that claimed censorship and 
other ideological attacks on public education by religious 
extremists and members of rightwing organizations occurred in 42 of 
the 50 states 
the report singled out 172 incidents that it said occurred during 
the 198889 school year comparing them with the 157 the group 
reported in 198788 
i want to emphasize that what is at stake in the battles being 
fought in communities across the nation is more than just the fate 
of a few novels or a textbook or two said john buchanan chairman 
of the group founded by television producer norman lear 
we are witnessing in these skirmishes the clash of two 
competing views of public education in america the censors see 
efforts to teach our children about the world around them as a 
threat the rest of us see it as a way to broaden our childrens 
vistas and opportunities 
sex education remains a major target by what the group described 
as the far right which already scored some damaging victories 
during the last school year the report said 
in south carolina for example the report cited statewide 
restrictions that forced school textbook publishers to delete 
information on the use of condoms to prevent the spread of aids 
there is a growing ultraconservative movement to restrict the 
availability of information in the school about such topics as 
contraception abortion and aids said president arthur kropp who 
predicted that attacks on sex education are likely to increase 
with recent supreme court rulings on reproductive rights 
the report said school libraries were the target of significantly 
more censorship attempts during the 198889 school year accounting 
for nearly half the challenges nationwide it said that most of the 
attacks it had investigated resulted in either removal of the 
material or in restrictions on its use such as requiring parental 
consent 
we are finding more and more instances in which selfappointed 
censors focus not just on material in the curriculum but on 
materials available in school libraries said kropp not content 
with sanitizing classroom teaching they want to scour the library 
shelvs of any materials of which they disapprove 
the main targets of such challenges were literary classics such 
as john steinbecks of mice and men and jd salingers the 
catcher in the rye as well as plays by arthur miller and 
aristophanes the report said 
the most frequent objections the report said were to materials 
seen as containing offensive language and those perceived as 
touching on satanism witchcraft and the occult challenges to 
satanism has grown over the last two years said donna hulsizer 
author of the report 
no challenges were reported in alaska delaware hawaii idaho 
minnesota new mexico north dakato utah or the district of 
columbia the report said it said california led the nation with 
what it called 23 censorship attempts 
