assassinations capped by the slaying of a highly popular 
presidential candidate sen luis carlos galan on aug 18 
hundreds of homes office buildings and other properties owned by 
traffikers have been impounded along with cars aircraft yachts and 
other goods the army estimates the value of the property at more 
than 200 million several midlevel trafficking suspects have been 
arrested 
