<TEXT>
with aids appearing in many countries the 
national council of churches is expanding efforts to inform 
missionaries about the virus and how to reduce risks of contracting 
it 
member denominations are being provided with educational 
materials special sterilized injection kits and other resources for 
missionaries as they are sent to their fields 
the risk of aids is real for missionaries serving in infected 
areas but not very high if a person takes precautions says dr 
john frame ncc consultant on health affairs 
of 40000 american protestant missionaries serving overseas six 
are known to have been infected with the aids virus four of them 
stationed in africa and two in the caribbean 
another missionary a hemophiliac infected through a transfusion 
died of aids in australia frame says 
the risk to missionaries is almost certainly related to 
profession medical or events that cannot be predicted such as 
accident or complications in pregnancy requiring blood 
transfusions he says 
there is also the risk of getting an injection from 
inadequately sterilized equipment 
</TEXT>
