believer that a person once saved is always saved 
tilley says he agrees that all believers are eternally 
secure but that people can revert into unbelief and deliberately 
renounce salvation he says this view is compatible with the 
eternal security of the believer since the apostate would no longer 
be a believer 
a faculty affairs committee recommended that tilley be retained 
