america is changing and not for the better 
wes jackson of the land institute salina kan a nonprofit 
research organization said in the reports introduction that the 
countryside represents the vulnerable soft underbelly of us 
society at large 
the simple reality is that rural people are a dispersed 
minority with no political clout marginal isolates rapidly becoming 
like third world peoples he said and increasingly the 
landscapes on which they live take on a third world appearance 
